### Key Findings

- **Backend is largely done.** `routers/nudges.py`, `routers/preferences.py`, `weekly_briefing.py`, and `preference_sweep.py` are all implemented. The remaining work is primarily frontend UI + browser push plumbing.

- **#285 (nudge banners)**: Build a custom React banner component (not a toast library). `GET /api/nudges` returns up to 3 nudges — wire dismiss (`POST /nudges/{id}/dismiss`) and stop (`POST /nudges/{id}/stop`). The 3/day limit is already enforced server-side.

- **#286 (preference toasts)**: A lightweight custom Tailwind toast (no library needed) for 4-second auto-dismiss preference-learned events. Confidence indicators use existing `emerging/moderate/strong` labels from `preferences.py` — map to amber/green/bold-green.

- **#287 (push notifications)**: Requires `pywebpush` (not in `requirements.txt` yet) + VAPID key generation + `push`/`notificationclick` handlers in the existing service worker + two new FastAPI endpoints (`/push/subscribe`, `/push/vapid-key`).

- **#288 (weekly digest)**: `weekly_briefing.py` already exists; work is surfacing it as a card in the briefing view.

### Gaps

- `pywebpush` missing from `requirements.txt` — must be added for #287
- VAPID keypair not yet generated — needed before push notifications work
- Existing service worker has no `push` event handler yet
