### Key Findings

**HIGH — Frontend `stopNudgeType` has zero test coverage (criticality 7)**
The store action gained toast-queuing + `fetchBriefing` side-effect, but `store.test.ts` was not updated. Three scenarios need tests: (1) preference toast added on success, (2) no toast for unknown nudge type, (3) optimistic nudge removal. Easy to add using the `vi.stubGlobal('fetch', ...)` pattern already in `store.test.ts`.

**MEDIUM — Unknown nudge type doesn't assert `preference` absence (criticality 5)**
